  "original_title": "\u0b87\u0bb0\u0bbe\u0b9c\u0bbf\u0ba9\u0bbe\u0bae\u0bbe \u0b95\u0b9f\u0bbf\u0ba4\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bcd \u0b95\u0bc8\u0baf\u0bc6\u0bb4\u0bc1\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9f \u0b9c\u0ba9\u0bbe\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0baa\u0ba4\u0bbf",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "The President signed the resignation letter",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "It has been reported that President Gotabaya Rajapaksa has resigned from his post.",
        "Our sister newspaper Daily Mirror reported that he signed the letter of resignation dated tomorrow (13) yesterday (11).",
        "The message indicated that the President's resignation letter had been signed and handed over to a senior government official, who would hand it over to the Speaker.",
        "Earlier, it was reported that President Gotabaya Rajapaksa had left the country. However, sources close to the president denied this and confirmed to the Daily Mirror that he is still in the country and is being protected by the armed forces.",
        "Shortly before the July 9 demonstration, the President was evicted by security forces from the Presidential Palace in the Fort. After that, he was secured in a naval ship within the country's territorial waters for security reasons.",
        "However, sources close to him said that the President had a direct meeting with the three military commanders at 9.30 am yesterday and that he has been in the country since then.",
        "His exact whereabouts in the country are unclear, but he is likely to leave the country this week, paving the way for a new president to take office and form an all-party government."
      ],
